e socialist/labour cause, these writings demonstrate his efforts to reconcile competing factions in the service of common aims.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh1 aBoos, Florence, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z978311131826408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079764040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147445809240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474458092423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474458092/original  a978-3-11-079764-0  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131826-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131918-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023